// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// TermBlink-GPU
// A production-ready, sidecar-compatible terminal browser engine.
// Quick Start
// 1. Install Dependencies
// Linux/Mac:
// chmod +x scripts/setup.sh
// ./scripts/setup.sh
// 
// Windows:
// .\scripts\setup.ps1
// 
// 2. Build & Run
// cargo run --release -- --fps 30 [https://webgpu.github.io/webgpu-samples/](https://webgpu.github.io/webgpu-samples/)
// 
// 3. CLI Options
// Flag
// Description
// Default
// --url
// Target URL
// WebGPU Samples
// --width
// Internal Viewport Width
// 1280
// --height
// Internal Viewport Height
// 720
// --fps
// Target Frame Rate
// 15
// --quality
// JPEG Quality (1-100)
// 50
// Integration (Sidecar Mode)
// TermBlink is designed to be bundled with other CLI tools.
// 1. Copy the termblink-gpu binary to your app's bin folder.
// 2. Run the setup script during your app's installation.
// 3. Spawn the process with stdio: inherit.
